commit.message:
Corrected a long-standing error in which ending text with a literal
backslash generates output that cannot be correctly read back in
because the backslash-parenthesis gets treated as a literal
parenthesis instead of a PostScript string delimiter.

Overwriting Makefiles again after merging pull request #15 from
github;  these really should be in .gitignore, as should
config.status. . .
Updated config.guess
Re-ran aclocal and automake on an updated system.

Updated version to go along with the merge of the pull request #11
from Eastdong (on Github).  The pull request fixes missing string
literals in a handful of sprintf() statements.
fix format not a string literal and no format arguments [-Werror=format-security]

Corrected what looks like a very long-standing error in the default
key bindings, in which Shift-Hold-Button1 performs a basic select
function instead of a select-box function.

Realized what the underlying cause of crashing on undefined "dpy"
was and fixed it at the root of the problem.

One more check on valid display which is known to be in the startup
path.

Continuing to track down the issue with a crash on startup on
certain window managers.  Apparently certain calls can be made
before the display is active.  Likely this is not the final fix.

Modified the UGetCursor() routine to return a valid response if the
TkWindowId is NULL do to lack of a mapped X11 window.

Changed the calls to Tcl_GetVar2() to keep the compiler from issuing
a warning.

Modifed some files to make the scrollbar widths scale with the
font sizes and icons, depending on screen resolution.

Applied one other trick to use the Tk command "font measure" to
determine the pixel size of the default font, and to size up the
icons to match, automatically.  This avoids issues with trying to
force a setting from the .xcircuitrc file.

Changed the handling of resources in the "resource.tcl" file to
change all fonts to "TkDefault" types.  This prevents all the
menus and windows from having text that is sized too small for
a high-resolution display.  Also added an XCOps(scale) that will
force a scaling of the icons and can be set in the .xcircuitrc
file.

Corrected error that can cause a crash on "library copy" if nothing
is selected.

Fixed filelist.c to prevent a segfault that occurs if an invalid
directory is entered into the file list entry box on the first try.

Made a change to the font loading with XLoadQueryFont() to fall
back on absolutely anything available (4th attempt).  And if that
fails, it issues a stern warning about not having any X11 fonts
available.

Corrected a PCB netlisting error where code failed to check for
a net count of zero and therefore attempted to access a non-
existing pointer.

Applying patch from Dan Moore's commit on github to correct for
a problem with pointer sizes that needs to be handled in the
code for Tcl_GetHandleFromObj().

Corrected the SVG output for text characters "<" and ">" to the
html encodings "<" and ">", respectively, per the bug
report from Henk Boezen.

Corrected an error where a label is incorrectly unselected when
"Parameterize" has been called from the menu while the label is
being created, causing a crash.  In the same place in the code,
corrected the position of the text cursor to account for the
added parameter start and end markers.

Added the ability to mark object instances as non-netlistable on a
per-instance basis (supplements the ability to mark objects as non-
network, which makes all instances automatically non-netlistable).
There is no method to make non-network objects netlistable on a
per-instance basis, only vice versa.

Corrected an error in the PCB netlisting which could cause nets to
get scrambled (in particular, regular nets could get merged into
global nets such as Vdd and Gnd by accident).

Corrected the wrapper, which had not updated the starting index
for colors since a new pre-allocated color was added (which was,
actually, quite a long time ago).  This prevents the "new window"
and "close window" options from working properly, as Tcl throws
an error when an image for a non-existent color button is
referenced.

Made another correction to the arc decomposition for path drawing;
this one is more fundamental than the last error, which was only in
the cairo code.  This one failed to add a line to an arc in a path
if the arc's start point differed from the previous path point.  That
led to a difference in behavior between xcircuit and PostScript.
Also found that the curve approximation of arcs was not handling
conversion to integer properly and so was generating slightly
incorrect curve approximations to arcs due to roundoff error.  Thanks
to Edgar Olthof for pointing out the error and providing detailed
examples.

Corrected an error in the cairo graphics implementation of the path
drawing routine, which fails to draw a line to the first point of a
curve if the curve first point is not the same as the previous path
point.

Corrected one missing void declaration on a routine in Xw (largely
deprecated, but still. . . ), and checks for NULL areawin in two
places pertaining to batch mode use.  Thanks to Kevin Zheng for
the patch.

Updated version to trigger a new tarball after handling github
pull request from Agustin Campeny.
Added extension for latex '\includegraphics{}'
